<div class="card">
  <div class="card__body">
    <h2>Purpose</h2>
    <p>These terms explain how data responsibilities are divided between HelloDeploy and users who deploy applications on the platform.</p>

    <h2>Platform Account Data</h2>
    <p>For HelloDeploy account, project, deployment, billing-free quota, support, audit, and security data, HelloDeploy determines the purpose and means of processing as described in the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

    <h2>User Application Data</h2>
    <p>For data collected by an application you deploy through HelloDeploy, you are responsible for your application&rsquo;s legal basis, notices, consent, security, retention, deletion, and data subject requests. HelloDeploy provides hosting and deployment infrastructure and processes application data only as necessary to run, secure, troubleshoot, and administer the platform.</p>

    <h2>Processing Activities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Building and deploying your repository.</li>
      <li>Injecting encrypted environment variables at runtime.</li>
      <li>Routing traffic to your application.</li>
      <li>Collecting deployment, health-check, and sanitized runtime logs.</li>
      <li>Performing security, abuse, capacity, and incident response operations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Subprocessors</h2>
    <p>HelloDeploy may use infrastructure and service providers including MongoDB Atlas, GitHub, Resend, Cloudflare, Docker-related host components, and server hosting providers. These providers process data only as needed for their infrastructure function.</p>

    <h2>Security Measures</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Password hashing with Argon2id.</li>
      <li>Encrypted environment secret values at rest.</li>
      <li>Secure HTTP-only session cookies.</li>
      <li>CSRF protection and rate limiting.</li>
      <li>Container isolation and resource limits for deployed applications.</li>
      <li>Audit logging for privileged actions.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Deletion and Return</h2>
    <p>When an account or project is deleted, HelloDeploy will delete associated platform records within the retention periods described in the Privacy Policy unless retention is required for security, abuse prevention, legal compliance, or dispute resolution.</p>

    <h2>Support for Requests</h2>
    <p>If you receive a request from an end user of your application and need platform-level assistance, contact <strong>hensonsagorsor@gmail.com</strong> with the project slug, affected data category, and requested action. Do not send secret values.</p>
  </div>
</div>
